        "created_at": "2024-12-17T17:41:59.117Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Currently when you search messages, long press a message and choose ‘select’ you will enter multi-select mode, but that dismisses the search you were preforming.</p>\n<p>This make it impossible to search messages and forward or delete a bulk selection of the search results.</p>\n<p>Suggestion:<br>\nThere is no room real estate to combine the keyboard, the search result and input bar and the action options all together.</p>\n<p>However when entering multi-select, we could stay in search mode and just add a button “done selecting” after which the search options make place for actions to preform. Additionally there could be a “back to search” button to dismiss the actions and go back to search while persisting the current selection.</p>\n<p>Back wnd forth options between multi-selecting in search and multi-selecting with actions.</p>\n<p>This goes well along with a different feature request to not dismiss a selection after choosing the forward option, so that one could forward the current selection and than continue to delete or modify the existing selection.</p>",
